<TEXT>
Lights across
the Esk
THREE bridges spanning the River Esk at Musselburgh are to be illuminated in a
bid to brighten East Lothian's reputation as a tourist destination.
The #133,000 project to light up the Short Hope Street Bridge, the Roman
Bridge, and the New Bridge is funded by the region and Lothian and Edinburgh
Enterprise Ltd.
Homicide charge
A MAN was committed for trial at Edinburgh Sheriff Court yesterday, charged
with the culpable homicide of unemployed chef George Bissett, 40, in the city's
Royal Mile on December 16. Mr Barry Elder, 27, of Penicuik, was remanded in
custody after a private hearing.
Prize motor
FIREFIGHTER Graham Atwell, of Glasgow's Yorkhill fire station, has won a Skoda
car in a Highway Code computer quiz he entered at the recent Scottish Motor
Show.
Exposed
A MAN who indecently exposing himself to a woman police officer in the
capital's Lovers Loan, Robert Patton, 33, was put on probation for two years at
Edinburgh Sheriff Court yesterday, on condition that he undergoes psychiatric
counselling.
Buildings saved
DUMBARTON District Council has allocated #90,000 for essential repairs to two
historical buildings: Woodbank, at Balloch, an eighteenth-century mansion
which, as a country hotel, ran into financial trouble in 1981, and the old
buildings of Dumbarton Academy.
Drugs missing
A WARNING has gone out after four ampoules of the drug Alfentanyl were stolen
from Edinburgh's City Hospital over the Christmas holiday. Alfentanyl is an
analgesic used as an anaesthetic in operations. If taken incorrectly it can
lead to unconsciousness.
Pub fire
POLICE are treating as suspicious a blaze that extensively damaged the Doocot
public house in Ferry Road, Edinburgh, early yesterday.
Relatives sought
POLICE yesterday appealed for help to trace relatives of an 80-year-old man
being cared for in a Glasgow's Gartnavel Royal Hospital. The man has given his
name as David McKinnon and his date of birth as April 1914.
Dead man named
A SCOT found dead in the yard of the Sun Inn at Shipley, West Yorkshire, on
Tuesday was named by police yesterday as Mr James Milligan, 61, from West
Lothian. A 19-year-old man was still being interviewed at by police.
Jewellery raid
TWO masked raiders robbed a 50-year-old woman and her 21-year-old daughter at
gunpoint in their home on Christmas Eve in Pollokshaws Road, Glasgow. They
escaped with more than #70,000 worth of jewellery and cash.
Fire victim
A WOMAN who died in a fire in a Glasgow tenement flat early yesterday has been
named as Maureen Harte, 48, of Birness Drive, Pollokshaws. She was alone in the
flat at 249 Allison Street, Govanhill, when the blaze broke out.
</TEXT>
