<TEXT>
Paper ruse
MUNICH: A German security van driver helped himself to an early Christmas
present by grabbing #1m from his vehicle and replacing the cash with scrap
paper, police said. His firm, near Munich, did not find the paper shreds until
Wednesday. The driver is thought to have fled the country.
Activists arrested
LAGOS: Five pro-democracy activists in Nigeria have been arrested over a banned
rally. They are thought to include the acting leader of the Campaign for
Democracy pressure group. Meanwhile, Nigeria has been excluded from a
Commonwealth meeting of parliamentary Speakers in Cyprus next week because of
human rights abuses.
Killer wolf loose
BUDAPEST: People in the Hungarian town of Pecs were warned to stay indoors
after a wolf escaped from a zoo. It killed an elderly woman, seriously injured
three children, and bit several other people in nearby woods.
</TEXT>
