<HEADLINE>Police link gun incidents</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>JAMES FREEMAN, Home Affairs Correspondent</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974651421</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
POLICE are linking two gun incidents in Lanarkshire on Wed-nesday night, the
first in which a shotgun was fired through the lounge window of a house in
Hamilton and the second, half-an-hour later, in which a car was hijacked at
gunpoint on the A8.
In the first incident, the lounge window of a house in Abbotsford Avenue,
Hamilton, was shattered after a shotgun was fired at close range.
Three people were in the living room at the time - two women and a man - but
none was injured.
Thirty minutes later, a 35-year-old man who stopped at the scene of an accident
on the A8 near Calderbank was robbed of his vehicle after being threatened with
what appeared to be a shotgun.
</TEXT>
