<HEADLINE>news digest</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<FLAG>news digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974651436</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Winter warmers
INMATES and staff at Polmont Young Offenders' Institute, near Falkirk, are to
send 1000 tartan prison blankets, which have been replaced by duvets, to
refugees in Bosnia.
More beds
ORTHOPAEDIC services at the Vale of Leven Hospital are to be improved with the
creation of more beds at a cost of #600,000. This will mean that routine
surgery currently carried out in Glasgow can be undertaken locally.
Roll of honour
EDINBURGH'S Heriot-Watt University is to award honorary degrees to nine public
figures, including doctorates to Sir David Steel and ex-world champion grand
prix driver Jackie Stewart, at its 1996 graduation ceremonies.
</TEXT>
