<HEADLINE>Yachtswoman to try again</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>BREWSTER SAMANTHA SAILING</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974651455</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Solo yachtswoman Samantha Brewster, 28, whose record attempt to sail round the
world the ``wrong way'' had to be halted earlier this month when her 85ft mast
broke, is to try again. She hopes to restart the 27,000-mile voyage on New
Year's Day from Santos, in Brazil, where she has been making repairs.
</TEXT>
