<DOCID>GH951229-000074</DOCID>
<DATE>951229</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Cricketer on the road to fame</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974651563</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
England wicketkeeper Jack Russell may have a street named in his honour in his
home town of Stroud, Gloucestershire.
The town already has a Russell Street in memory of its nineteenth-century MP
and later Prime Minister, Earl Russell. Now it is proposed to change the name
to Jack Russell Street to mark Stroud's pride in its cricketing hero.
</TEXT>
