<TEXT>
BRIAN WILSON was somewhat selective in his quote from Hamish Henderson's Ballad
of the Men of Knoydart (December 22).
The opening quatrain of an earlier verse runs:
I'll write to Arthur Woodburn,     boys,
And he will let you know,
That the Sacred Rights of     Property,
Will never be laid low.
Arthur Woodburn was Secretary of State for Scotland in the post-war Labour
Government.
Neil R MacCallum,
18 Redford Avenue,
Edinburgh.
